## Plan

**Approach:** Extend `printRunDetail` in `internal/cli/run.go` to render a gates
section after the stages loop, only when `len(m.Gates) > 0` (so v0/v2 runs and any
zero-gate run print byte-identically to today â€” no empty header). Match the existing
flat `fmt.Fprintf` + two-space-indent idiom used for stages exactly (no tabwriter;
that is only used by `run list`). Render gates in manifest/append order (the order
capture-gate wrote them, which is already chronological per (phase, round)); do not
re-sort. Keep it a readable, scannable summary: status/tier/reviewed-stages on the
gate header lines, one block per seat with provider/model/harness + verdict, and
required-feedback bullets + failure_note + degraded/escalation reasons only when
present. No `--json`, no verbosity flag (out of scope). Provider/model/harness are
always set on seats per the schema (validateSeat requires harness.name + provider),
so render them unconditionally; required/optional/failure_note/decision reasons are
optional and printed only when non-empty.

Chosen rendering (one gate, mirrors the plan.r1 fixture):

```
gate: plan.r1
  phase:    plan
  round:    1
  tier:     2
  status:   rerun
  reviewed: plan (role=plan)
  degraded: pilms reproducible 0-CPU hang; resolved on rerun
  seat: gemini
    provider: google / gemini-3.1-pro-preview
    harness:  gemini-cli 3.1
    verdict:  block
    required:
      - backfilling old run != AC#4 new-run
      - test ref-mutating push script in throwaway repo first
      - verify local append before push
  seat: opus
    provider: anthropic / claude-opus-4-7
    harness:  claude-code opus-4-7
    verdict:  go
  seat: pilms
    provider: lmstudio / qwen/qwen3.6-35b-a3b
    harness:  pi x
    verdict:  disregarded
    note:     0-CPU client hang; LM Studio backend healthy
```

Rules per element:
- Gate header: `\ngate: <gate_id>` then indented `phase`, `round`, `tier`, `status`.
- `reviewed:` one line per ReviewedRef as `<stage>` plus ` (role=<role>)` when Role
  set and ` (artifact=<sha>)` when Artifact set; omit empties.
- Decision: print `escalation:` when EscalationReason set, `degraded:` when
  DegradedReason set, `deferred:` (comma-joined) when DeferredBeads non-empty;
  skip the whole block when GateDecision is zero-valued.
- Per seat: `  seat: <seat>`, then `provider: <name> / <model>`, `harness:
  <name> <version>` (drop trailing space when version empty, like the stage harness
  line). `model:` is NOT added separately (provider already carries it). `skill: <id>`
  IS rendered conditionally when `SeatResult.Skill.ID` is non-empty (a reviewer seat
  may carry a skill/tool identity; raw model seats like the dogfood reviewers usually
  leave it empty, so the line is omitted then â€” mirrors how the stage block treats an
  empty skill and how `note:`/`raw_output:` are conditional). Then `verdict: <verdict>`;
  `required:`/`optional:` as ` - ` bulleted sub-lists only when non-empty;
  `note: <failure_note>` only when set; `raw_output: <path>` only when RawOutput != nil
  (summarized as the artifact path, not dumped inline).

